actually documented, was it,

00:02:00.220 --> 00:02:01.320
how it was executed?

00:02:01.320 --> 00:02:04.907
So we felt it was OK to change
the implementation because we

00:02:04.907 --> 00:02:07.570
weren't actually violating any
contracts that we've made.

00:02:07.570 --> 00:02:09.080
But yeah, essentially, because
it broke stuff.

00:02:09.080 --> 00:02:10.575
